{
  "texts": [
    "The noise identification task also forms a new synthetic data which represents \"noise\" and \"clean\" data.",
    "The \"clean\" labeled data is the data directly used as it is from the dataset, whereas the \"noise\" data is a data altered by inserting, swapping or deleting 10% of the tokens from the source data.",
    "The aim of this task is to predict whether the entry is \"clean\" or \"noise\" data.",
    "Negative log likelihood is used as objective function in this self-supervised task.",
    "The aim of employing the self-supervised tasks is to learn a domain independent information."
  ]
}